                        <interp inst="t18381231-name-77" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM GREEN</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with Mr. Booth, of Princes-street I was standing by Mr. Painter's gig, and saw the prisoner take the cloak, and give it to another boy—they both ran off—a woman picked the cloak up at the corner of the street—I had not seen it dropped—about a quarter to seven o'clock the same evening, I was going on an errand, and saw the prisoner walking down Princes-street, with another boy—I followed him to Tothill-street, and gave him in charge.</p>
